criteria.driver_alignment:
Discover — defined the question and buyer tradeoff ("what enterprise value KKR should bid...");  
Represent/Validate — ran and reported multiple valuation methods and ranges (DCF, trading comps, precedents) and sensitivity to synergies;  
Implement/Reflect — executed the model, reflected on DCF vs. market-clearing precedents and recommended a sponsor bid range and walk-away.

Represent — defined the model requirements (5-year forecast, margin ramp, reinvestment);  
Implement — referenced running code and scenarios to produce outputs;  
Validate — triangulated DCF, trading comps, and precedents and presented base/downside/upside valuations.

Discover — framed the question and inputs (DCF, comps, precedents) and objectives;  
Implement — explicitly referenced code and running the model;  
Represent/Validate — described outputs, charts, and numeric ranges (base/downside/upside) and triangulated results;  
Reflect — drew recommendation and negotiating strategy from the results.
